With your code, the records will be added only when you do a `GET /generate`, so it&#39;s normal that your database is empty when you run the application.
If you want to preload the database with some records, I suggest the creation of a configuration class like this :

    @Configuration
    public class LoadDatabase {

        @Bean
        CommandLineRunner initDatabase(MyRepository repository) {
            return args -&gt; {
                repository.save(...);
            };
        }
    }

This way you will not have to make a request to your API each time you want to generate your database.

From your description i understood you have two issues.

1) DB Tables not getting created.

I had same issue and i tried by changing my db config like this has solved db creation issue.

    spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/myDbSchema?createDatabaseIfNotExist=true
    spring.datasource.username=root
    spring.datasource.password=
    spring.datasource.driverClassName=com.mysql.jdbc.Driver
    spring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.MySQLDialect
    spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create
    spring.profiles.active=prod

2) This application has no explicit mapping for /error, so you are seeing this as a fallback.

Here spring boot is trying to look for page named as &#39;error&#39;. So that means I think  you are using Spring MVC. so if any error occur at runtime, MVC view resolver will look for error page.

and your error message also showing &quot;There was an unexpected error (type=Not Found, status=404).&quot; so i am suspecting that it is trying to look for page named as &quot;GENERATED SUCCESSFULLY&quot; for no exception case or &quot;Failed&quot; for exception case and it does not find that page that is why it gives error code 404

If you want to just return plain string then change your get api like below.

